wikipedia_page.main: Charles Moss (6 March 1882 – 25 July 1963) was an English road racing cyclist who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics. He was born in Ascott-under-Wychwood, Oxfordshire.He was part of the Great Britain team which won the silver medal in the team time trial. In the individual time trial he finished 18th.
